\section{Optimal evolution models for 2-level systems}\label{sec2}

Before introducing the main result let us make two remarks to explain the denotations.
\begin{rem}
In this section we assume that the Kraus operators which constitute a dynamical map for 2-level quantum systems are proportional to the Pauli matrices and the $2-$dimensional identity matrix. The Pauli matrices shall be denoted as $\{ \sigma_1, \sigma_2,\sigma_3\}$ and the corresponding identity matrix by $\mathbb{I}_2$. 
\end{rem}
\begin{rem}
