a_1 \neq a_2  \neq a_3  \label{eq:condition2}
\end{eqnarray}

In other words, the theorem claims that the generator of evolution corresponding with the dynamical map given by Kraus operators from \ref{eq:kraus2}-\ref{eq:kraus2con} has no degenerate eigenvalues provided the parameters $(a_1,a_2,a_3)$ fulfill the conditions \ref{eq:condition1} and \ref{eq:condition2}.
